d) EfectÃºe un clustering jerÃ¡rquico, interprete el resultado.

DM <- sym.dist.interval(sym.data = num_datos_sym, method = "Ichino")
model <- hclust(DM)
plot(model, hang = -1)

e) Investigue sobre el paquete RSDA si se puede aplicar kâmeans, de ser asÃ­ aplÃ­quelo.

library(fmsb)

grupos <- sym.kmeans(num_datos_sym, k = 3, iter.max = 10, nstart = 1, algorithm = c("Hartigan-Wong", 
    "Lloyd", "Forgy", "MacQueen"))

centros <- grupos$centers
rownames(centros) <- c("Cluster 1", "Cluster 2", "Cluster 3")
centros <- as.data.frame(centros)
maximos <- apply(centros, 2, max)
minimos <- apply(centros, 2, min)
centros <- rbind(minimos, centros)
centros <- rbind(maximos, centros)


color <- c("red", "green", "blue")
radarchart(as.data.frame(centros), maxmin = TRUE, axistype = 4, axislabcol = "slategray4", 
    centerzero = FALSE, seg = 8, cglcol = "gray67", pcol = color, plty = 1, plwd = 5, 
    title = "ComparaciÃ³n de clÃºsteres")
legenda <- legend(1.5, 1, legend = c("Cluster 1", "Cluster 2", "Cluster 3"), seg.len = -1.4, 
    title = "ClÃºsteres", pch = 21, bty = "n", lwd = 3, y.intersp = 1, horiz = FALSE, 
    col = color)
